by N. English and L. Wollersheim:

"a neo-enlightenment and neo-renaissance of science, consciousness and life. It is great shift and great turning toward a greater alignment based upon a unified understanding of the evolution of life and consciousness from the largest possible time and space perspective that exists--- the universe as a whole system perspective. We have arrived at a critical juncture in human history where it is prudent and critically necessary to expand the collective metaphors and worldview that informs our lives, values and ethics. We must look beyond our current cultural, political, economical partial views and perspectives. It is due time to facilitate a new framework of metaphors that we call the Unissance and a new worldview that we call the New Universe Worldview. This new worldview and Unissance is awakening individual and collective consciousness. It informs and habituates a sustainable global culture, includes and celebrates all of our collective partial views of the past, is in alignment with the science that we are just coming to know about ourselves and our universe and, it artfully and joyously reverences the miracle of our beingness in the universe."
(http://www.integrativespirituality.org/)


